The Federal Reserve is expected tointervene in the government securities market to add temporaryreserves via customer or system repurchase agreements,economists said.    Most economists said the Fed will inject reservesindirectly via customer repurchases, but they added that theFed might opt for a direct injection of reserves via overnightsystem repurchases.    Federal funds opened at 6-3/8 pct and eased to 6-5/16 pctin early trading. Funds averaged 6.29 pct yesterday. Reuter&#3;